  "page": "Zhea",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Zhea</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Zhea the Barren</li><li>Zhea Zorseface</li><li>Zhea the Cruel</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Jhattar\" title=\"Jhattar\">Jhattar</a></i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Jogos_Nhai\" title=\"Jogos Nhai\">Jogos Nhai</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Plains_of_the_Jogos_Nhai\" title=\"Plains of the Jogos Nhai\">Plains of the Jogos Nhai</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Zhea</b>, also known as <b>Zhea the Barren</b>, <b>Zhea the Cruel</b>, and <b>Zhea Zorseface</b>, was the first <i><a href=\"/index.php/Jhattar\" title=\"Jhattar\">jhattar</a></i> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Jogos_Nhai\" title=\"Jogos Nhai\">Jogos Nhai</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character\">Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zhea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Zhea was described to have been cunning.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf842_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf842-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zhea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Zhea was a woman of the <a href=\"/index.php/Jogos_Nhai\" title=\"Jogos Nhai\">Jogos Nhai</a> who chose the life of a male warrior. When a thousand rivals unified to fight against the massive army of <a href=\"/index.php/Lo_Bu\" title=\"Lo Bu\">Lo Bu</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/God-Emperor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"God-Emperor\">God-Emperor</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Empire_of_Yi_Ti\" title=\"Golden Empire of Yi Ti\">Golden Empire of Yi Ti</a> which threatened the hunt down the Jogos Nhai into extinction, they raised up Zhea as a <i><a href=\"/index.php/Jhattar\" title=\"Jhattar\">jhattar</a></i>. When Lo Bu divided his massive armies into thirteen hosts, Zhea isolated each of the emperor's armies, slaying their scouts and foragers, starving them, denying them water, leading them into wastelands and traps, and so each of the <a href=\"/index.php/Yi_Ti\" title=\"Yi Ti\">YiTish</a> armies was destroyed. Finally his riders descended on Lo Bu's own host. Lo Bu's severed head was presented to Zhea, who commanded that the flesh be stripped from the bone and his skull be dipped in gold and made into his drinking cup, which has passed from <i>jhattar</i> to <i>jhattar</i> through generations. To this day, Zhea is remembered in the Golden Empire, where mothers whisper his name to frighten unruly children into obedience.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf842_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf842-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zhea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf842-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf842_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf842_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; The Bones and Beyond&#32;(The Plains of the Jogos Nhai).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"wikitable succession-box noprint\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:small;clear:both;\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>New title</b>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b> <a href=\"/index.php/Jhattar\" title=\"Jhattar\">Jhattar</a> </b>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>Unknown</b><div style=\"font-size:90%\">Next known title holder:</div><b><a href=\"/index.php/Gharak\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gharak\">Gharak</a> </b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403113900\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.066 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.239 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 727/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 12641/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5251/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 487/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 10/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 619/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.150/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.45 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expan